Lulonke Saleni was last seen by his mother while playing with a friend in the Mangawungu informal settlement on Thursday afternoon. CAPE TOWN - Police said that a missing four-year-old boy from Philippi East was found unharmed and had been reunited with his family. Lulonke Saleni was last seen by his mother while playing with a friend in the Mangawungu informal settlement on Thursday afternoon. It's not yet clear where the child has been for the past few days.